Oliver C. PRESS, Plaintiff-Appellee, v. The PENNSYLVANIA RAILROAD COMPANY, Defendant-Appellant. No. 144. Circuit Court of Appeals, Second Circuit. Dec. 26, 1939. Burlingham, Veeder, Clark & Hupper, of New York City (Ray Rood Allen and C. B. Manley O’Kelley, both of New York City, of counsel), for appellant. Herbert Kaufman, of New York City (Jacquin Frank and Ralph E. Schneider, both of New York City, of counsel), for appellee.

Before SWAN, AUGUSTUS N. HAND, and PATTERSON, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Judgment affirmed.
